title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that checks the total purchases in 2025 from creditors with "VVS" in their name. It must also be creditors that do not have "SLETTET" in their name. Output in descending. I want creditor_id, creditor name and total price of each in my output. Output in textfile.

operations.table: (SELECT creditor_id, name FROM creditor) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val name = r.getField(1).toString.toUpperCase; name.contains("VVS") && !name.contains("SLETTET") }

operations.table: (SELECT creditor_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_price FROM factpurchases) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val d = r.getField(1); if (d == null) false else d.toString.startsWith("2025") }
(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => (r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int], r.getField(2).asInstanceOf[Double])
(t: (org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record, (Int, Double))) => { val credRec = t._1; val id = credRec.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = credRec.getField(1).toString; ((id, name), t._2._2) }
(a: ((Int, String), Double), b: ((Int, String), Double)) => (a._1, a._2 + b._2)
(t: ((Int, String), Double)) => { val id = t._1._1; val name = t._1._2; val total = t._2; (id, name, total) }

log.thoughts: Load creditors and filter by name containing VVS and not SLETTET, filter purchases to 2025, join on creditor_id, sum invoice_line_price per creditor, sort descending by total and write textfile lines with id, name and total.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT creditor_id, name FROM (SELECT creditor_id, name FROM creditor) as X) as X
(SELECT creditor_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_price FROM (SELECT creditor_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_price FROM factpurchases) as X) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val d = r.getField(1); if (d == null) false else d.toString.startsWith("2025") }
(t: (org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record, (Int, Double))) => { val credRec = t._1; val id = credRec.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = credRec.getField(1).toString; ((id, name), t._2._2) }
(a: ((Int, String), Double), b: ((Int, String), Double)) => (a._1, a._2 + b._2)
(t: ((Int, String), Double)) => { val id = t._1._1; val name = t._1._2; val total = t._2; (id, name, total) }

log.thoughts: Fixed ClassCastException by changing map (id=5) to robustly convert invoice_line_price (often java.math.BigDecimal) to Double and handle nulls; also ensured creditor name null-safety in downstream map. This minimal change avoids BigDecimal->Double cast errors during reduceBy.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0); val name = r.getField(1); if(id == null || name == null) false else { val nm = name.toString.toUpperCase; nm.contains("VVS") && !nm.contains("SLETTET") } }
(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val d = r.getField(1); if (d == null) false else d.toString.startsWith("2025") }

(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val idObj = r.getField(0); val priceObj = r.getField(2); val id = if(idObj == null) null.asInstanceOf[Int] else idObj.asInstanceOf[Int]; val price = if(priceObj == null) 0.0 else priceObj match { case bd: java.math.BigDecimal => bd.doubleValue(); case d: java.lang.Double => d.doubleValue(); case f: java.lang.Float => f.doubleValue(); case l: java.lang.Long => l.doubleValue(); case i: java.lang.Integer => i.doubleValue(); case s: java.lang.String => try { s.toDouble } catch { case _: Throwable => 0.0 } ; case _ => 0.0 }; (id, price) }

operations.thisKeyUdf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0); if(id == null) null.asInstanceOf[Integer] else id.asInstanceOf[Int] }
